{
  "image_id": "abc123",
  "detections": [
    {"id": 0, "box": [112,40,280,210], "label": "dog", "confidence": 0.94},
    {"id": 1, "box": [400,180,560,310], "label": "cat", "confidence": 0.88}
  ]
}
```

A **typed contract** (Pydantic model) validates every field's type/range at the boundary, gives you one source of truth that's versioned, and fails *loudly* on malformed output instead of letting a downstream consumer silently mis-read a missing or renamed field. In a chain of models, the contract between stages is what keeps a change in the detector from quietly corrupting the classifier's input — it's the API of your pipeline.
